text: Limnonectes deinodon is a species of fanged frogs in the family Dicroglossidae. It is endemic to peninsular Malaysia and likely also southern Thailand. It was previously confused with Limnonectes laticeps and Limnonectes khasianus. ==References== * *http://research.amnh.org/vz/herpetology/amphibia/Amphibia/Anura/Dicroglossidae/Dicroglossinae/Limnonectes/Limnonectes- deinodon Category:Limnonectes Category:Amphibians of Malaysia Category:Amphibians described in 2014
title: Limnonectes deinodon
